{
  "texts": [
    "RNNs and LSTM models excel in these scenarios by learning from historical data to predict future behavior (Wang et al. 2023a).",
    "For example, LSTM-based VAE-GAN (Niu et al. 2020) has been applied in telecom for detecting subtle, long-term anomalies in network traffic that traditional models may overlook.",
    "These models are particularly effective in detecting service disruptions or slow degradations that occur over extended periods.",
    "LSTM-based models have demonstrated significant efficacy in network anomaly detection, particularly in analyzing time-series datasets such as network latency and packet loss.",
    "Their adaptability in managing dynamic and fluctuating traffic loads makes them ideal for identifying unusual patterns that signal potential service disruptions."
  ]
}